  "decision_conditions": [
    "The provision of a raised terraced area at first floor level and privacy screening would form an unneighbourly feature which would impede outlook from first floor windows of the adjoining premises and present as an intrusive form of development contrary to the Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD and Policy DC61 of theLDF Core Strategy and Development Control Policies DPD.",
    "The development would create an uplift in occupancy and an intensification of the use of the site. This would present in increased comings and goings to the site which would be over and above what could be regarded as acceptable and would be through noise and disturbance be detrimental to the amenity of adjoining and nearby occupiers, contrary to Policies DC4 and DC61 of the LDF Core Strategy and Development Control Policies DPD.",
    "The development would fail to make adequate provision for off-street parking and it has not been demonstrated that any overspill could be satisfactorily accommodated. The proposed development would, by reason of the inadequate off-street parking provision result in unacceptable overspill onto the adjoining roads to the detriment of highway safety and the free flow of traffic contrary to Policy DC33 and the amenity of surrounding occupiers through increased competition for on-street spaces contrary to DC61 of the LDF Core Strategy and Development Control Policies DPD and London Plan Policy T6.",
    "Statement Required by Article 35 (2) of the Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015: Consideration was given to seeking amendments, but given conflict with adopted planning policy, notification of intended refusal and the reason(s) for it was given to the agent in writing 02-09-2021"
  ],
